+article('Splitting Exercise', '')
  +section('Splitters')
    .text
      :markdown
        # Split路ting Ex路er路cise

        This type of exercise is used in two forms: to split words in syllables or to place dividers in sentences.

        It shows a list of elements (e.g. syllables) and on top the separators are interleaved (e.g. ). Pressing (click or touch) a separator makes the separator to be placed or removed between nearby elements.

        The score is computed as a function of correctly placed separators vs. total number of separators. The wrong placements are subtracted from the score.

        Here are some examples:

      +exercise({name: 'ex7splitter'})
        +split-in-syllables({
          name: 'split-in-syllables-1',
          separator: '路', // or any html code. Undefined or falsy for '-'
          word: 'sy||l^^l||a^^b||le',
        })
          .score-box
          .progress-box
          .is-done-box
          .preview
            | Your result, mylord:
            span.result

        +split-in-syllables({
            name: 'split-in-syllables-2',
            separator: ',',
            word: 'Anna^^come|| outside^^ please!'
          })
          .is-done-box
          .score-box

        +split-in-syllables({
            name: 'split-in-syllables-3',
            separator: ',',
            word: 'I|| do not|| have|| time^^ Dan^^ I|| really|| do not.',
            isModal: true
          })
          .is-done-box
          .full-screen-header
            .is-done-box.inline-block
            span Place the commas
            span.small.result.sans
            .progress-box
          .preview
            .score-box
            | Your result, sir:
            span.result
